< name>
Daniel Yang<//name>
<review>I used to eat here regularly 5-10 years ago.  I stopped going because it always got so crowded, it just wasn't worth the wait.  Fast forward to 2017/2018.  I've been eating nothing but KHD Baekjong, Quarters, Parks, Soot Bull Jeep in Ktown in 2017.  I was doing weekly ventures to Ookook and Gen, and Red Castle bbq for all you can eat in 2015-2016.  I revisit this place 2 weeks ago, and I forgot how much I loved it.  The ban chan (side dishes) leave nothing to be desired. It's literally every side you need and want.  The thin cut brisket and pork belly are excellent.  The galbi (marinated short rib) is also good and all u can eat on our $21.99 per person option.  (There is a $19.99 dinner option that doesn't include the galbi and some other better cuts of meat).  The steamed egg and kimchi/soybean soup is also all u can eat, the limited sushi roll menu is all you can eat (I would stay away from these fillers, as they are packed with rice and not much of a step up from supermarket/buffet rolls) and they leave 2 carafes of water so you never have to ask for a refill.  After all is said and done, at this price point, it is truly my favorite.  Are there better places?  Of course.  Are there more expensive/cheaper places?  Of course. But everything here is everything I grew up on, and is what I expect Korean BBQ to be all about. Nothing more, nothing less.  And the price is fantastic.<//review></record>

< Text>
About 5 months ago we started looking for cabinets for our kitchen remodel. We came to ferguson after going to several other cabinet sellers. We decided on ferguson because they had what we needed and the price (a bit high but not enough to deter us ) fit in our budget. Our cabinets have been installed and look great. The people at Ferguson were helpful and always professional. We dealt with Doris mainly and she was professional but...we had issues.  She came to our home and brought a contractor (Jeramy) and after we agreed to work together we ordered the cabinets. Doris told us we would deal with the contractor separately so we did. The cabinets arrived on a Friday so I called Jeramy about my install and he said he won't be installing because something happened between him and Doris ( we never found out what). Doris called me and said she has someone else. Except he ONLY does cabinets. Hes not a contractor. He was great and installed them over a period of 2 weeks! He came on a Monday to install everything but then we waited another week for the pulls and plugs and trims to be installed because he had other jobs. We had to find a granite installer and a sink installer and electrician. It was awful and took 3 months. I would recommend ferguson but not the cabinet people. Maybe not the way it's usually done but I didnt feel good about the way we were treated. Cabinets look great though.</Text>

< Review>
I attended an event at the City View and had a great experience. Here's why:

1) Location: It's centrally located and an easy walk from many hotels.

2) Views: They have a beautiful outdoor patio with amazing views of downtown San Francisco.

3) Food: The catering was pretty good for a conference/event space.

4) Space: It's pretty large and can be used in a variety of ways.< /Review>

0x15325c2710b9c797:0xc498281f01084bf9<//GmapID>
<Pictures>None<//Pictures><Resp>None< /Resp>< Review>
This was the third time I've eaten there and the 1st time the chef has cooked the salmon to my liking. It was delicious! When I told the waiter to compliment the chef for me he said he would. He also said that Dino's has a new chef who is much better than the last. My vegetables were cooked to perfection as well. Since I have dietary restrictions I couldn't have any of the starch options, nor could I have the soup, so I asked for a double serving of the carrots and broccoli. Which the waiter was happy to supply. The salad was fresh, and crisp. The dressing was served on the side as requested.

Although parking in front was limited, two patrons were leaving just as I was arriving. Dino's also has additional parking in the back. They should post a sign to that effect.

Although we were a large group everyone was given pleasant and prompt service. I didn't hear any complaints about the food except about the calamari. It seemed to taste of ammonia. Stronger to some than to others.

Dino's is located in Castro Valley, if I were in the neighborhood I would eat their again.

The atmosphere is family friendly. They have two rooms. One for serving normal sized groups and the other for private parties, such as ours.</Review>

<user_name>Dan Homerick< /user_name><Date>1515817622568< /Date><rate>4</rate>< text>
Great service, pretty low prices for dine-in fare, but the food was merely okay. If price is a big concern, then this place is still a big step up in quality from something like Denny's, with only a little step up in prices; at least, if you catch their early bird menu (4-6 pm), as we happened to. We've only been the one time, and so can't comment on their regular menu's prices.

The atmosphere is a bit neglected. It's not unpleasant by any means -- no harsh lighting, or uncomfortable chairs -- but it looks like it could use some freshening up.

The clientele, at least at 6 pm on a Friday night, was mostly retired couples. No one seemed to mind us strolling in with our five-year old, though.< /text>

< text>
Their Al pastor isn't really Al pastor, it's carnitas. Their marinade is not Al pastor marinate, nor is the meat spit roasted. Unless they made a mistake on my order and gave me carnitas. The burrito was pretty big for $5.75, and it was ok, nothing to boast about, but a 11:30 pm, it did its job. The tacos were pretty good, albeit, the meat was a tad bit dried. Not bad when you want a quick Mexican fix late at night. But I would not come here during the day when better options are available.<//text>

< Review>
Horrible experience there. I deliver for Post Mates and Door Dash and this is the ONLY place I've been to where they can't figure out how to charge for the food. It's happened 3 separate times when they are not able to process the transaction after me having waited for at least 15 minutes because of how slow they are. This last time, they charged me the wrong amount and when they tried to charge the correct amount, the card wouldn't go through anymore. They wanted me to pay out of pocket for the difference. Why would I pay out of pocket for food that wasn't even mine? They rather lose the sale and waste the food then just give me the food minus the 2 dollars that was due, even though it was their mistake in the first place! I ended up having to cancel the order, so I wasted 30 minutes of my time and didn't get paid anything due to their incompetence. They shouldn't be offering food delivery if they can't get it together there!! Extremely upsetting!<//Review>

< Text>
This is one of my favorite places to go to get authentic Spanish food. I love their weekend mornings buffet. They catered an event I went to and that was awesome as well. The Chile Verde pork burrito with no beans and rice but with queso is my ultimate favorite. Watch out it is HOT! But that makes it so good because you cant stop eating even though it burns!! I love it! Their drinks are amazing too. The horchata is already an over the top favorite but their Peppino "cucumber" lemonade, tamarind, and Jamaica juices are the best in the business. The best in the western region Nv, Az, and Ca. Love this place!!!</Text>
